-- Sample rows now carry a per-column SOURCE label, and the workbooks ship a PROVENANCE sheet.
--
-- The table showed 59 census columns with no indication of where each value came from. Each column
-- that is drawn from a reference source is now labelled beneath its header (O*NET for title/SOC,
-- BLS OEWS for wage figures, Census/ZCTA for state + ZIP), so the data explains itself on the page
-- the same way the downloaded .xlsx now does via its PROVENANCE sheet.
